com.vmware.vapi.server.cert

Interface CertificateCache

  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.util.function.Supplier<java.util.concurrent.CompletionStage<java.security.cert.X509Certificate[]>>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    CertificateCacheImpl

    public interface CertificateCache
extends java.util.function.Supplier<java.util.concurrent.CompletionStage<java.security.cert.X509Certificate[]>>
    Cache of certificates. Must be thread-safe.

    The implementation could be synchronous or asynchronous - what is appropriate depends on your vAPI server setup.

      • get

        java.util.concurrent.CompletionStage<java.security.cert.X509Certificate[]> get()

        Specified by:
        get in interface java.util.function.Supplier<java.util.concurrent.CompletionStage<java.security.cert.X509Certificate[]>>

      • refresh

        void refresh()
        Starts refresh of the cache. When this method exits, refresh could still be running. After this method exits, all subsequent calls to get() must return the refreshed certificates.
